1. DEFINITIONS
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1.1 "Work" (Licensed Material) means the work, content, code, documentation, media, and other
copyrightable material to which the Licensor has applied this License, including any accompanying metadata,
embedded assets, and repository materials. For repositories and hosting platforms (including github.com), the
Work includes, to the extent copyrightable and included by the Licensor under this License: source files,
binary files, documentation, README content, LICENSE text, examples, prompts, configuration, build scripts,
issues, issue comments, pull requests, pull-request comments, commit messages, release notes, tags, wiki
pages, discussions, gists/snippets, CI/CD workflow files (including GitHub Actions workflows), and attached
artifacts/media. The Work also includes any portion of the foregoing when shared separately.

1.2 "Share" means to provide material to the public by any means requiring permission under copyright,
including reproduction, distribution, public display, public performance, or making available online.

1.3 "Adaptation" means copyrightable material derived from or based upon the Work in which the
Work is translated, altered, arranged, transformed, or otherwise modified in a manner requiring
permission under copyright. A compilation or aggregation that includes the Work unmodified is not
an Adaptation.

1.4 "NonCommercial" means not primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or
monetary compensation.

1.5 "Effective Technological Measures" ("ETMs") means measures (e.g., DRM) that, in the absence of
proper authority, may not be circumvented under laws implementing WIPO Copyright Treaty Article 11
and/or similar provisions.

1.6 "Attribution LTHING" means a machine-readable LTHING document meeting Section 3.2. LTHING is a
cryptographic trust format based on a YAML-derivative, employing post-quantum primitives: SHAKE512
(custom Keccak-f[1600] with c=1024, r=576, 512-bit security), ML-DSA-65 (FIPS 204, NIST Level 3),
and Deoxys-II-256-128 (CAESAR finalist AEAD). LTHING utilizes high-resolution temporal data (64-bit
millisecond epoch), masked through a Rule 30 cellular-automaton salt stream, to establish Proof of Time,
securing data against Store-Now-Decrypt-Later (SNDL) attacks and retroactive forgery.

1.7 "Independent Module" means a work that:
(a) contains no portion of the Work (including verbatim or near-verbatim code, text, assets,
    documentation, examples, prompts, or embedded excerpts);
(b) is not an Adaptation of the Work; and
(c) merely interoperates with, extends, or communicates with the Work via separable interfaces
    (APIs, file formats, protocols, plug-in hooks, CLI invocation, network calls, or other separable coupling).

1.8 "Affiliate" means any entity that directly or indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common
control with You. "Control" means power to direct management or policies (by ownership, contract, or otherwise).

1.9 "Module Production Team Headcount" means the total number of unique natural persons who materially
contributed labor to the design, development, testing, documentation, packaging, release, maintenance,
marketing, sales, support, or distribution of the Independent Module, whether compensated by salary,
hourly pay, contract, revenue share, equity, barter, or unpaid arrangement, and whether acting directly
or through an intermediary entity. One person counts once even if they fill multiple roles.

1.10 "Gross Revenue" means total gross revenue in USD (or USD equivalent) for the relevant fiscal year,
aggregated across You and Your Affiliates.

1.11 "No Descriptive Locator Allowance" means that any required location reference in this License must be
a URL/URI only; descriptive phrases such as "see README," "GitHub repo," "Nature article," "the folder,"
or other non-URI pointers do not satisfy the requirement.

1.12 "Epoch Rule30 Salt Stream" means a deterministic byte stream derived as follows:
(a) take the current Unix epoch milliseconds (64-bit integer);
(b) encode the value as canonical UTF-8 bytes with an explicit field label;
(c) initialize a Rule 30 one-dimensional cellular automaton seed from those bytes;
(d) evolve Rule 30 for a fixed, documented number of rounds and extract bytes from its state;
(e) use the extracted bytes as salt material and as the keystream source described in Section 5A.3(e); and
(f) XOR (or equivalently stream-cipher mask) the epoch millisecond value bytes with the Rule 30 keystream to produce the
    epoch-masked value used in the hash provenance record.

1.13 "Original Creator" means the Licensor (l'Evermoor) and any person or entity explicitly designated by the
Licensor in writing as an original rights-holder for the Work. For clarity, the NonCommercial restriction in
Section 3.3 does not limit the Original Creator's own right to sell, license, or otherwise monetize the Work
or Adaptations.

